{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"initAsync","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"ioPriority","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"callback"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_async_initable_new_async()"},{"type":"text","text":" should typically be used instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When the initialization is finished, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"callback"},{"text":" will be called. You can","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_async_initable_init_finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" to get the result of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initialization.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization, the error","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notSupported"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As with "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true},{"text":", if the object is not initialized, or initialization","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"returns with an error, then all operations on the object except"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_unref()"},{"text":" are considered to be invalid, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have undefined behaviour. They will often fail with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_critical()"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_warning()"},{"text":", but this must not be relied on.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be initialized multiple times; for more information, see "},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"implementation requires yielding all subsequent calls to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init_async()"},{"type":"text","text":" on the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"results of the first call."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For classes that also support the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" interface, the default"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"implementation of this method will run the "},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in a thread, so if you want to support asynchronous initialization via"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads, just implement the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","isActive":true},{"text":" interface without overriding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"any interface methods."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Starts asynchronous initialization of the object implementing the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interface. This must be done before any real use of the object after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"initial construction. If the object also implements "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" you can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"optionally call ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"t